Chief Executive Officer of Toll Brothers Inc (NYSE:TOL), Yearley Douglas C. Jr., sells 345 shares worth $13,715
According to Toll Brothers Inc's most recent Form 4 filing with the SEC dated Jun 29 04:50 PM, company Chief Executive Officer, Yearley Douglas C. Jr. disclosed selling 345 shares at a cost of $39.75. At the time of this transaction (Jun 28), this trade was worth $13,715 in total. As of Jun 28, Yearley Douglas C. Jr. now owns 186,027 shares in total worth about $7,366,669.2. 
For the last few recent trades made by Toll Brothers Inc (NYSE:TOL) Chief Executive Officer, Yearley Douglas C. Jr., we have the following information:




SEC Form 4 filing: Jun 02: Sold 10,000 shares at the rate of $38.50 per share. Total worth of this trade was $385,029. Total number of shares owned as of Jun 02 were 186,372
SEC Form 4 filing: Mar 08: Sold 8,250 shares at the rate of $36.00 per share. Total worth of this trade was $297,000. Total number of shares owned as of Mar 08 were 196,372
SEC Form 4 filing: Feb 23: Sold 8,000 shares at the rate of $34.05 per share. Total worth of this trade was $272,400. Total number of shares owned as of Feb 23 were 196,372




